High school pupils from seven schools in Manenberg have shown they can still achieve their goals despite their circumstances. CAPE TOWN - The Cape Town community of Manenberg has become synonymous with crime, gang violence and drugs. But high school pupils from seven schools in the area, have shown they can still achieve their goals despite their circumstances. Top matric achievers with more than a dozen distinctions among them have been honoured by the community at a public gathering. READ: Manenberg fighting back against gang violence They were taken through the streets where gang violence is rife. Their aim: To show the community what they have achieved at school. They were awarded certificates and gifts, including laptops and power-banks.